<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f105129558116126>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=4442&mid=105129558116126>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=4442&mid=105129558116126>Guide To Get Pants</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=4442&mid=105129558116126#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Apr 25th 3:11 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=192354><span id=Scholar>Bigskyn</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>46 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>These are not too hard to get with a decent group in the 40's. The quest is a little time-consuming but very worth it for leather-wearing classes.<br><br>HOW TO: Either buy or get a blood wolf harness in the Great Divide. BW is tougher than his bretheren so if you have a tough time with the normal dire wolves, bring friends.<br><br>Second, forget Dracnia in Crystal Caverns. Kill a few dozen orcs there instead and eventually you will get a bottle of Karsin Acid (no drop/lore). You can take this into the turn-in guy in thurgadin (in the bar). Hand him the bottle and he will drop a gem of persuasion into your inventory. No faction hit for doing this.<br><br>Third, give the BW harness and gem to Vorhees in the coldain hut just off from the velium river south of the southern entrance to the wurm caves. You get the control harness.<br><br>Fourth, get your group together and have them get ready to go to the entrance to the GD giant fort (the one facing the POK book and spires). Then the fun begins.<br><br>Fifth is turning in the control harness to brood mother. This can be a little tricky as some of the elder and ancient shardwurms see through invis and cammo. I found that going high up on the side walls to skirt the wurms often worked. They have a low aggro-radius so you either get around or get hit and run back out of the caves. They wont follow very far. Camp to clear aggro and try again.<br><br>The easiest way to find the Broodmother for the hand-in is to go in the northern entrance (near Thurg). Take the first left and when you come to the first fork she is in the cavern straight in front of you. She is flanked in a closer cavern by two guardian shard wurms. The guardians do not see through invis and BM will not aggro you.<br><br>At this point yell at your friends to get over to the fort. Uninvis, hand BM the harness and she will slowly march off to the giant fort. Takes anywhere fomr 2-5 minutes as she sometimes wanders.<br><br>In the meantime, invis up and just run straight back out the way you came. You may get popped by a wurm, but just keep running because (again) they will not follow you far. Get to the fort to help your group.<br><br>THE FORT/Battle: Grakl and Fergul the giants will respawn inside the fort and saunter out front to the gate. If you are looking at the gate from the outside, they will turn on the outside wall and take up a position just off the corner of the fort closest to the wurm caves. Grakl is in gold and Fergul is in silver. <br><br>What will happen is that the brood mother will come up and start a fight with Grakl. Fergul will take off running toward the EW zone. He is the one you need to kill to get the legs, but if you attack him before he starts to run the leggings do not drop. His path is straight along the fort wall toward the EW zone. If your group sits at the opposite corner from where the giants stopped you will have an easy attack point.<br><br>Can be a tough fight and watch out for adds, but lots of fun. Remember not to attack Fergul till he runs AFTER the wurm attacks grakl. Enjoy your new pants :)</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Bigskyn Biggerheart: <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=478057" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=478057</a></td></tr>
