	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=139867><span id= >trystdare</span></a><br><span id=notbold>24 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;Myself (53 Shaman) and a 45 Ranger, 45 Monk (well equipped) did this quest yesterday.  I had the Ranger track everthing and make sure it was all in order before we began, then I left Ranger and Monk at entrance to fort to watch and make sure no one bothered the spawn.  We did this during the middle of the day CST and I spent 5 minutes ahead of time spamming the zone with /ooc about what I was going to do and what the zone should NOT do (this is more key than anything else).  When all was ready I invised and wandered into the Cave.<br><br>  I had never been in the cave before and most of the wurms near the entrance were lite blue to me.  I had no map (Get one from EQAtlas when you do it) and just turned down the first side passage I came to.  Now I noticed it get unusually dark (being a Barbarian Shaman with limited dark vision) but I could just make out the tunnel walls and the looming dark blue mobs that were in abundance.  I tried one room and only found a static spawn of 4 blue non named mobs, then down another passage (my heart beating now hoping invis holds) and another room with a static non named until finally I see the BM at the back of a cavern with two blues near the entrance.  I moved behind her next to the wall and handed in the item invis, she took it and started walking away and I hit invis and took off running for the exit.  Just my luck I got turned about in the dark and ended up in a dead end with my heart in my throat thinking invis would drop, I would have to gate out(bound in Firepot room), or just die. Luck was with me and I made it out then turned the wrong way and started running towards Thurg instead of to Fort (I was a bit excited), came to my senses and ran to the fort spamming my partners to not attack until I say so and to the zone to not agro or bother the BM or go near the fort (this is very important).<br><br>  The two giants walk outside the fort and stand to the side and wait for the BM, I got there just as she walked up and poked the one giant with her toothy maw and Fergul took off running.  I spammed &quot;GET HIM NOW&quot;  to my crew and they aggroed him right next to the BM, I cast Slow and he came after me so I led him to the side where we felt a little safer (kind of scary fighting next to the BM) it was an enjoyable fight.  The Ranger and Monk did massive DPS and I slapped a few heals on them, rooted an add, and re-hasted.  Took about 5 minutes to drop him, he has a good amount of HPs and I did not dot (wanted to save mana for heals and slows).  When he fell we all let out a woot and I let out a double woot when I saw the legs, quest done perfectly thanks to the below step by step guide.<br><br>  Thanks to Xatrik and Zendiil for being my tanks.  If you are on Xegony and want some help doing your legs, look me up, I will help you out.<br><br>Sequi Sicarius<br>Clan MacLear<br>Xegony<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sat Nov  9 15:33:14 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
