	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=147411><span id= >Frekkels</span></a><br><span id=notbold>1 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Got my legs on E. Marr last night.&nbsp;&nbsp;(2/27/02)<br>Not as easy for me as some of the people posted here mentioned.  The hardest part of the whole ordeal for us was getting TO the broodmother.  Without some help, it would have been impossible.<br><br>Had a friendly exp group move to the fort to keep the 2 FG's at entrance cleared and watch for other groups.  Unfortunately, they had a wipeout right before I turned in the harness. :(   Nevertheless, I think this helped reduce our adds before the Fergul battle.<br><br>Getting to the BM was difficult because the elders and ancient Wurms kept seeing through invis and aggroing.  Shardtooth was there too, so at least one of my guildies got a good tunic out of it also.  I eventually had to call on more guild reinforcements to clear the cave out as much as possible.  Had an enchanter, druid, and necro (average 50+) helping.  Druid died once after a huge 7 wurm train.  We had been trying to enter the cave from the Thurgadin side, but eventually gave up and ran to the other end.  Worked a little better that way.<br><br>Turn-in went w/o a hitch, used the following to keep strangers from screwing quest up:<br>/ooc PERFORMING QUEST! Please leave BROODMOTHER,  GRAKL, and FERGUL alone.  Thanks for your cooperation.<br><br>My server is relatively civilized. Only one person came up to get BM before I performed turn-in, but respected my camp.  One group started to help us take down Fergul, but stopped after we asked them not to.  Your mileage may vary.  Repeated the /ooc a few times as we progressed through zone w/ BM in tow.<br><br>The Broodmother became an Elder Wurm pet for a minute (freaked me out), but my Necro friend feared the elder and I regained control.  That happened right outside the cave entrance.  The pathing for BM was a bit screwy.  We feared or rooted anything in front of BM while I stayed as close behind her as possible w/ SoW and Invis up.<br><br>BM engaged Grakl, though despite my THOROUGH briefing ahead of time, my necro buddy drew aggro for a minute.  He died when a few strays added. :(<br><br>I lost complete sight of Fergul during this, but luckily my druid friend tracked and rooted him.<br><br>After leading a small FG train around after a wrong turn(leaving them in the dust), I finally found my friends and Mr. Frostsky. ;)<br>Druid was almost oom (from previous Wurm/FG encounters).  Enchanter and I ping-ponged Fergul w/ dots on and no problems right at the wizard spires.<br><br>As an aside, there was another group or two who were working n the quest (earlier step) at the same time but had trouble with the Vores turn-in.  I had no problems, but I did the turn-in for the harness of control about 2 weeks ago.<br>Kind of funny that there were like 3 petitions in on this quest at the same time.  2 ppl complaining about it being broken, and mine saying it is working.<br><br>LONG overdue replacement for my Tribunal Imbued Ringmail leggings. :D  I'm very happy. :)<br><br>Take care,<br>Frekkels. Forgotten Guard member on E. Marr<br>Barbarian Shaman of the 44th Circle<br><br>PS:  BIG thanks to Biano, Darria, and Uurson for guild support on this, and another thank you to Theis, Rabbidd, and Khedive for keeping the fort entrance cleared as much as possible.  HUGE thanks to Kraphalis for the rez's afterwards.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Feb 28 09:13:41 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
